The paper deals with optimizing the operation and performance of a wireless small cell network (SCN) that encompasses multiple mobile network operators (MNOs) using a novel framework based on matching theory. The paper focuses on the resource management of millimeter wave (mmW) multi-hop backhaul networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also considers economic factors during network formation and resource management, which suggests that it could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT) or game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper deals with the wireless channel characteristics of the mmW backhaul network, which could place it under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or signal processing (cs.SI).
